    "long_instructions": "# Data Policies\r\n\r\n#### Data policies can provide a sense for what kinds of information is actually being collected by modern computing innovations like websites and apps. Practice your own data privacy reading skills by choosing a technology you use on a regular basis and responding to the questions below.\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8148B2; display: inline-block;\">\r\n    ➡️ This activity is from Lesson 2. You can find more details in the full <a href='https://example.com/lesson1' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>Lesson Plan</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n#### Even if you can’t find information, you should record where you looked and the fact that you can’t find it. If there isn’t a policy or it’s hard to find, that can be just as interesting as seeing the policy itself.\r\n\r\n- #### **Question 1**: What kinds of data is collected?\r\n- #### **Question 2**: How is the data you listed above being used? What features are enabled by the data?\r\n- #### **Question 3**: Does the company share the data with anyone else? Who?\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8148B2; display: inline-block;\">\r\n    ➡️ If you have time, check out the full <a href='https://docs.google.com/document/d/1v4Q2dsV0zJCh1zgcP3mwKu-iIsn9gl7v5-ZDwYMlSMs/edit?tab=t.0' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>Activity Guide</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n",
